title: The Americas
subTitle: The Gulf Coast, where swamps and wetlands shelter black bears and alligators; manatees gather in freshwater springs, burrowing owls look for love in the suburbs and a rare ocelot raises her kittens in Texas' thornscrub.

title: Crocs of Katuma
subTitle: Follow the story of two mothers, a crocodile and a hippopotamus, as they face the perils of raising a family in this beautiful, remote location of Katuma.

title: Tiger Guards Of Kanha
subTitle: Forest guards and patrolling officers at Kanha Tiger Reserve highlight the history since its inception and talk about the gruesome attacks on the staff.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: Travelling to some of the world's major forests and jungles, providing a complete view of their wildlife, biodiversity and importance for life on the planet.

title: Parenthood
subTitle: Water is essential to all life on Earth, but too much or too little can be disastrous. Parents must master timing to overcome freshwater's constant change and successfully raise the next generation.

title: Wild Italy: Top Predators
subTitle: In the heart of the Mediterranean, the team enters into a special world where bears and eagles live free among the vestiges of a distant past, making it a veritable treasure trove of biodiversity.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Tiger Guards Of Kanha
subTitle: Explore the activities in a day of a tiger guard who faces various challenges on daily patrol. Also discover how one guard survived a bear ambush while on duty.

title: Chasing the Rains
subTitle: Observes the innovative teams working to preserve and protect Kenya's wildlife, deploying such tools as a radio-tracking-collar system.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: In the slippery rock-lined Sand River, John Varty struggles to save an enormous two-tonne bull giraffe that's gone down and can't get up.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: The forests that grow in the dry and mountainous regions of Madagascar. They are home to the ring-tailed lemur, pied crow, species of tenrec and unique chameleons.

title: Wild Assassins
subTitle: Explores the various techniques that wild animals use to hunt for their prey in order to survive, including venom, camouflage, and expertise in hide and seek.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: In the centre of South Africa is an ancient landscape that was once an inland sea. Now it is a mosaic of unique habitats. Life here has evolved ingenious solutions to survive. There is nowhere in South Africa quite like the Karoo National Park.

title: Parenthood
subTitle: Parenting in the ocean demands dedication and intelligence. From navigating the reef, to teaching young to hunt giants, these parents have remarkable strategies.

title: Okavango: River of Dreams
subTitle: Special episode going behind the scenes to reveal the events that took place during production, highlighting a journey filled with dramatic moments, humour and and more.

title: Zambia Untamed
subTitle: As temperatures soar, lagoons and waterholes are drying up. This forces Mvula and his family to undertake a long and dangerous journey to the only remaining source of water, the Luangwa River.

title: New Kids in the Wild
subTitle: In Brazil's Serra da Capivara, a troop of capuchin monkeys welcome their latest member, baby Chico, who soon explores a forest full of excitement and danger whilst learning key skills that will allow him to survive and thrive.

title: Chasing the Rains
subTitle: Observes the innovative teams working to preserve and protect Kenya's wildlife, deploying such tools as a radio-tracking-collar system.

title: Extreme Snakes
subTitle: Meet Africa's diverse but often dangerous species of snake, which have evolved to thrive in the myriad habitats existing within this vast, biodiverse continent.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: The Southern Drylands is a journey into the most arid and extreme environments in the furthest reaches of southern Africa. Spectacular but treacherous places where almost no rain falls with incredibly resilient creatures.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Desert animals have evolved to handle heat and lack of water. This includes scorpions, which have existed since life first crawled from the sea.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: The African Savannah sees thousands of battles each day. Learn how elephants survive on a diet that even the strictest vegetarian would avoid.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: Cameras capture the beauty, diversity and richness of the world's forests and jungles.

title: The Americas
subTitle: The Andes, Earth's longest mountain range; baby bears make treacherous descents, rare hummingbirds compete for mates, frogs freeze and revive, and lizards battle for territory -- all in a land of extremes, from glaciers to deserts.

title: Lion Country: Night and Day
subTitle: Conclusion of the groundbreaking documentary series. As the rainy season approaches, the young cubs of both prides are put in jeopardy.

title: The Story of Cats
subTitle: The first episode looks at big cats in Africa and South East Asia. Lion whisperer Kevin Richardson proves how similar our pets are to the fearsome big cats and why there is more to feline communication than meets the eye. In the thick jungles of South East Asia, the sabre-tooth wild cat has given domestic tabbies their gravity-defying climbing skills, and in Namibia, a strange looking cat called a caracal has given them the ability to jump over three metres and catch birds in flight.

title: Lion: The Rise and Fall of the Marsh Pride
subTitle: The Marsh Pride of lions in Kenya's Maasai Mara Reserve. This tale of shifting loyalties, bloody takeovers and sheer resilience is told by those who filmed them for over 30 years.
